           {:role "user"
            :content "Teacher Request:
            {{request}}

            Mandatory Request Requirements:
            The request MUST explicitly include:
            Topic
            Number of slides
            Make sure that you understand what teacher wants: explanation, examples, taks, quiz, homework or something else
            if not sure do not assume ask
            Example Teacher Request: I need 3 tasks on Present Simple use food for vocabulary in the tasks
            So you dont need to create explanation, examples but tasks

            General:
            - Do NOT use linguistic jargon beyond the specified CEFR level
            - Content must be culturally neutral and suitable for PowerPoint slides
            - Examples if exist must strictly follow the grammar rule and be realistic classroom sentences
            - Definitions should be clear and at the right difficulty level
            - Topics should be relevant and useful for language learning

            Class Configuration:
            - Language: {{language}}
            - CEFR Level: {{level}}
            - Age Group: {{age-group}}

            STRICT VALIDATION — check each field one by one before generating anything:
            1. Topic — is the subject of the slides clearly stated?
            2. Number of slides — is an exact number explicitly given? Do NOT pick a default.
            3. Content type — does the teacher say what kind of slides they want?
               (vocabulary definitions, grammar explanation, tasks/exercises, quiz, homework, or other)

            There are exactly TWO valid responses:

            A) If ANY of the three fields is missing or unclear — return ONLY:
              {\"requirements-not-met\": \"Your clarification question written in the same language as the teacher's request.\"}
            Ask only about what is missing — do not repeat what is already clear.
            Do NOT assume defaults. Do NOT infer missing values.

            B) If ALL three fields are present and clear — generate the slides immediately.
            Return ONLY the slides JSON in the format below. No confirmation step. No intermediate message.


            Native Language Rule:
            - If Native Language Setting = \"No\" → do NOT include translations.
            - If Native Language Setting = a language → include a \"translation\" field inside each slide object.

            Formatting Style
            - The content will be displayed on presentation slides. Write for scannability, not paragraphs
            - Use short lines, not long sentences or paragraph
            - Use line breaks to visually separate sections and ideas
            - Use symbols to create visual structure: headings (\uD83D\uDCCC), bullet points (\uD83D\uDD39), positive (✓), negative (✗), questions (?), arrows (→) for relationships or transformations
            - Group related items together with clear spacing between groups
            - Keep each line to one idea or one form pattern
            - Make the content easy to read at a glance from the back of a classroom
            - Definitions: one clear, concise sentence — no long explanations
            - Examples: short, natural sentences that help students remember the word in context
            - Make each field easy to read at a glance from the back of a classroom

            Since you generate text-only slides, visual structure must be created through:
            Symbols (✓ ✗ →)
            Clear grouping
            Pattern formatting
            Transformation arrows

            Student Working memory is limited. Overloaded slides = poor learning.
            Implications for your
              One grammar idea per slide
              5–7 lines max
              Avoid long paragraphs
              Avoid too many examples at once
              Avoid mixing rule + exceptions + irregular forms on same slide.

            Break complex or complicated into small units.
            Example Instead of:
              Present Simple – Full Explanation
              Break into: Use Form Third person rule Negatives Questions
              Each = separate slide


            Format the response as a JSON object with this exact structure:\n{\n  \"title\": \"topic title\",\n  \"subtitle\": \"Level: {{level}} | number of slides\",\n  \"slides\": [\n    {\n      \"slide-title\": \"slide title\",\n      \"content\": \"generated content \"\n    }\n  ]\n}
          "}]
